				<div id="recipe101cb"></div><div id="wprm-recipe-container-20649" class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="20649" data-servings="12"><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"http:\/\/schema.org\/","@type":"Recipe","name":"My Favorite Pumpkin Bread (Kabocha + Dark Chocolate)","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Heidi Swanson"},"description":"This is a maximalist pumpkin bread for anyone wanting to bake a knock-out version. Vibrant color comes from kabocha squash, exceptional moistness from olive oil, and bittersweet chocolate and cacao nibs offset and balance the sweetness. If you love pumpkin bread, this is a special one.","datePublished":"2026-02-27T16:12:28+00:00","recipeYield":["12"],"prepTime":"PT45M","cookTime":"PT90M","totalTime":"PT135M","recipeIngredient":["One 1-Ib \/ 455g piece kabocha squash, seeded","1 cup plus 1 tablespoon \/ 235 g extra-virgin olive oil, plus more for drizzling","1 1\/2 cups \/ 187 g unbleached all-purpose flour","1 1\/2 teaspoon baking powder","1\/2 teaspoon baking soda","1 tablespoon ground cinnamon","2 teaspoons freshly grated nutmeg","3\/4 teaspoon fine grain sea salt","1 1\/3 cups \/ 265 g granulated sugar","3  large eggs","8 oz \/ 230 g bittersweet chocolate, finely chopped","1 1\/4 cups \/ 150 g confectioners' sugar, sifted, plus more as needed","2 tablespoon \ufeff\ufeffhot water, plus more as needed","2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil","2 tablespoons crushed cacao nibs","3 tablespoons well-toasted pepitas, cooled"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Preheat the oven to 425\u00b0F \/ 220\u00b0C with a rack in the middle. On a baking sheet, drizzle the squash with olive oil, turn the piece cut-side down, and cook until very soft and beginning to caramelize where the squash touches the pan, typically 30 minutes or so. It\u2019s ok if there are super toasty bits. Remove from the oven and let cool. Scrape out the flesh and transfer to a food processor. Pulse until smooth. Measure out 1 cup \/ 225g. Save any leftovers, refrigerated, for another use.","name":"Preheat the oven to 425\u00b0F \/ 220\u00b0C with a rack in the middle. On a baking sheet, drizzle the squash with olive oil, turn the piece cut-side down, and cook until very soft and beginning to caramelize where the squash touches the pan, typically 30 minutes or so. It\u2019s ok if there are super toasty bits. Remove from the oven and let cool. Scrape out the flesh and transfer to a food processor. Pulse until smooth. Measure out 1 cup \/ 225g. Save any leftovers, refrigerated, for another use."},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Preheat the oven to 325\u00b0F \/ 165\u00b0C.  Butter and line a 9-by-5-in loaf pan, or equivalent smaller pans (see notes in main post) with parchment paper.","name":"Preheat the oven to 325\u00b0F \/ 165\u00b0C.  Butter and line a 9-by-5-in loaf pan, or equivalent smaller pans (see notes in main post) with parchment paper."},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt into a large bowl. In a medium bowl, whisk together the granulated sugar, olive oil, squash pur\u00e9e, and eggs. Make a well in the center of the flour mixture and pour in the squash mixture. Whisk until just combined. Stir the chocolate into the batter.","name":"Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt into a large bowl. In a medium bowl, whisk together the granulated sugar, olive oil, squash pur\u00e9e, and eggs. Make a well in the center of the flour mixture and pour in the squash mixture. Whisk until just combined. Stir the chocolate into the batter."},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Pour the batter into the prepared pan (or pans) and bake until browned on the top and a skewer inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean (important), 80 to 90 minutes (or more) - or, about 55 minutes for a trio of smaller pumpkin breads. Let cool in the pan on a wire rack for 15 minutes. Run a knife around the edges and use the parchment to tip the cake from the pan. Let cool on the rack completely before icing. Set the rack on a parchment-lined, rimmed baking sheet for easy clean-up, in case the glaze runs over.","name":"Pour the batter into the prepared pan (or pans) and bake until browned on the top and a skewer inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean (important), 80 to 90 minutes (or more) - or, about 55 minutes for a trio of smaller pumpkin breads. Let cool in the pan on a wire rack for 15 minutes. Run a knife around the edges and use the parchment to tip the cake from the pan. Let cool on the rack completely before icing. Set the rack on a parchment-lined, rimmed baking sheet for easy clean-up, in case the glaze runs over."},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"To make the glaze: In a small bowl, whisk the confectioners' sugar with the 2 tablespoons of hot water until you have a thick glaze. Slowly whisk in the olive oil. Pour the glaze over the cake(s), allowing it to drip over the sides a bit. Right away, sprinkle with the cacao nibs and pepitas and let the glaze set completely before serving, an hour or so.","name":"To make the glaze: In a small bowl, whisk the confectioners' sugar with the 2 tablespoons of hot water until you have a thick glaze. Slowly whisk in the olive oil. Pour the glaze over the cake(s), allowing it to drip over the sides a bit. Right away, sprinkle with the cacao nibs and pepitas and let the glaze set completely before serving, an hour or so."}],"recipeCategory":["Brunch","Cake","Dessert","Fikka","Kid-friendly","Sweets"],"recipeCuisine":["American","Baking","California"],"keywords":"pumpkin bread","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"526 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"62 g","proteinContent":"6 g","fatContent":"30 g","saturatedFatContent":"9 g","transFatContent":"0.01 g","cholesterolContent":"41 mg","sodiumContent":"230 mg","fiberContent":"2 g","sugarContent":"42 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"19 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"image":["https:\/\/images.101cookbooks.com\/PUMPKIN-BREAD-h.jpg?w=1200&auto=format","https:\/\/images.101cookbooks.com\/PUMPKIN-BREAD-v.jpg?w=1200&auto=format","https:\/\/images.101cookbooks.com\/PUMPKIN-BREAD-v.jpg?w=1200&h=1200&fp-z=2&fp-y=.5&fp-x=.5&fit=crop&crop=entropy"]}</script>
				<h2>My Favorite Pumpkin Bread (Kabocha + Dark Chocolate)</h2>
				<div class="cb101-recipe-main">
	<div class="cb101-recipe-image-container d-flex justify-content-between p-3">
